## Report: `requiredIf` design investigation

**1. MapSchema structure** (`/app/src/schema/map/schema.ts:7-98`)

```ts
export class MapSchema<ATTRIBUTES extends MapAttributes = MapAttributes, PROPS extends SchemaProps = SchemaProps> {
  type: 'map'
  attributes: ATTRIBUTES
  props: PROPS
  keyAttributeNames: Set<string>
  savedAttributeNames: Set<string>
  requiredAttributeNames: Record<SchemaRequiredProp, Set<string>>   // computed in constructor + re-verified in check()
  constructor(attributes, props) { ... }
  get checked(): boolean { return Object.isFrozen(this.props) }
  check(path?: string): void { /* validates props, dedups savedAs, freezes attrs/props */ }
}
```
`requiredAttributeNames` buckets attribute names into `'always' | 'atLeastOnce' | 'never'` by reading each attribute's `attribute.props.required` (default `'atLeastOnce'`). `attributes` is a plain object `Record<string, Schema_>`, so a sibling attribute name is just `Object.keys(this.attributes)` — trivial to type-check against with `keyof ATTRIBUTES`.

**2. Builder pattern — no shared base class.** Every leaf/composite schema *duplicates* the same `required`/`optional`/etc. methods on its own `*Schema_` class (no mixin/trait). Found via `symnav resolve 'required'`:
- `src/schema/map/schema_.ts:57-68`, `src/schema/item/schema_.ts` (likely similar), `src/schema/any/schema_.ts:48-52`, `src/schema/anyOf/schema_.ts:48-52`, `src/schema/list/schema_.ts:63-67`, `src/schema/record/schema_.ts:73-81`, `src/schema/set/schema_.ts:60-64`, and each primitive's `schema_.ts` (string/number/boolean/binary/null) at lines ~51-55.

Canonical pattern (`src/schema/map/schema_.ts:57-68`):
```ts
required<NEXT_IS_REQUIRED extends SchemaRequiredProp = AtLeastOnce>(
  nextRequired: NEXT_IS_REQUIRED = 'atLeastOnce' as NEXT_IS_REQUIRED
): MapSchema_<ATTRIBUTES, Overwrite<PROPS, { required: NEXT_IS_REQUIRED }>> {
  return new MapSchema_(this.attributes, overwrite(this.props, { required: nextRequired }))
}
optional(): MapSchema_<ATTRIBUTES, Overwrite<PROPS, { required: Never }>> {
  return this.required('never')
}
```
Every builder method is **immutable**: it calls `overwrite(this.props, {...})` (`src/utils/overwrite.ts`) — a plain `{...a, ...b}` shallow merge typed via `Overwrite<A,B>` — and constructs a new schema instance carrying `this.attributes` untouched. `requiredIf` would follow the exact same shape but must also update the `PROPS` type with the new field(s) it introduces (e.g. `requiredIf: [string, unknown[]]` or similar), and would need `ATTRIBUTES` in scope to constrain the attribute-name argument type-safely (`keyof ATTRIBUTES`), which only map/item builders have — primitives/anyOf/etc. don't know siblings, so `requiredIf` naturally only makes sense on `MapSchema_`/`ItemSchema_` (attributes referencing their own siblings), not standalone leaf schemas, unless attached as a prop on the child schema that the parent map interprets.

**3. State/props representation.** `SchemaProps` (`src/schema/types/schemaProps.ts:23-37`):
```ts
export interface SchemaProps {
  required?: SchemaRequiredProp   // 'never' | 'atLeastOnce' | 'always'
  hidden?: boolean
  key?: boolean
  savedAs?: string
  keyDefault?: unknown; putDefault?: unknown; updateDefault?: unknown
  keyLink?: unknown; putLink?: unknown; updateLink?: unknown
  keyValidator?: Validator; putValidator?: Validator; updateValidator?: Validator
}
```
`props` is stored per-schema-instance (each `Schema_` extends its non-builder `Schema` base holding `props: PROPS`), validated by `checkSchemaProps` (`src/schema/utils/checkSchemaProps.ts:16-73`, includes `schemaRequiredPropSet`), and frozen on `.check()`. A `requiredIf` field would be added to `SchemaProps` (e.g. `requiredIf?: [string, ...unknown[]]`) and validated similarly in `checkSchemaProps`, plus cross-checked against sibling attribute names inside `MapSchema.check()`/`ItemSchema.check()` (where `this.attributes` is available) rather than in `checkSchemaProps` itself (which only sees the single schema's props, not siblings).

